values: this weekend was good, it was very relaxing. on friday i went to work then i came home becasue i was really tired. saturday i just sat around and worked on some homework then i went to see fun with dick and jane which really wasn't that good. after the movie i went to laurens they got a new puppy and he was so cute. i stayed at laurens till like 1 then i came home and on sunday i went to see my dad and went shopping then i went to work. now i'm here in class doing nothing.

it has been a long time since i updated, i just got done with my adv. computer exam, so now i only have ap english and physics. well, not much has been going on, nothing that is worth writing about, paw paw lost to mattawan so bad yesterday it was horrible, oh well, everyone thought they would. well, i got to go, bye

well, i haven't updated in a while, not much has been going on. Thanks to everyone who came to my suprise party. Kelly, i loved the harry potter candy and the gift certificate. it was really fun, thanks for everything, well, i'm in computers so i got to go, bye.

new layout for the new year! 

birthday countdown 9 days!
[mood| full] [music| spice girls] Merry Christmas to everyone i hope you all got great presents!

well, this weekend was fun, i was so busy. on friday i had to babysit for powless's kids and some other kids. i left there at like 11 then i went to bed. on saturday i had to work from 10-3 then i went to brianne's her mom did my hair. she did a good job, i liked it. then we went to formal. it was the best one so far except that my date didn't want to be there and wouldn't dance. after the dance i went home and then on sunday morning i went with haleigh and bri to kzoo heat tryouts. it was a lot of running, i don't think i'll make it. but who knows. well i got to go. bye.

so far this weekend has been good. 

wednesday night i went bowling with nicole and then spent the night there. we woke up at noon and then i came home. i ate dinner at my aunts, and my family was up from georgia and florida so that was cool. after dinner i went home for a while then i went to alisons at like midnight. she fell asleep but i stayed up until we left for shopping at 4. when we got to best buy the line went around 3/4 of the building, but somehow when we got in the store we were like 6th in line for the ipods. they didn't have the 4 gb nana which was what ali wanted, but they had the 60 gb video so i got that. then we went to target and got ali's ipod. then we went to circut city, old navy, walmart, office max, and mc sports. it was fun, we got back at like 9 o'clock and then i finally fell asleep. now i'm awake and doing nothing.

so nothing much happened today. we had practice at 10 which i liked a lot better than practice at 9. Anywho, after that i went shopping with ali and mary in grand rapids. i got a dress, but i don't really like it. i might wear ashley's i don't know yet. i also need to find a date for formal, but that issue could be a whole nother post. after shopping i went home for about 6 seconds then i went to lauren's house with ashley, megan and patience were there and we played games. now i'm back at ashley's and were going to watch desperate housewives because she has never seen it before. 

Harry potter count down. 6 days!

so this weekend was pretty fun. On friday the football team lost, but afterwards i went to see Saw 2 with Ashley, Trevor and John. it was funny, i think ashley watched like 2 minutes of it.

on saturday i went shopping with alison and farah. that was fun. we didn't find anything though. then we met todd and paul at the theatre and they actually carded us so we couldn't go in. So we all went over to brianne's house. we watched deuce bigalow, the first one. that was fun. anyway, later that night i went to nicole's party. that was fun. me, emily, grace, and colleen spent the night. we went to bed at like 2 when david left. on sunday i had to go work at the theatre.

today i have my harvard inerview at 3 then practice at 4. that's about it.

so i'm sitting here in student assistant and being bored. we won last night, i only played like a minute and a half and now my mom is mad and wants me to quit basketball because it is a waste of time and money.

tommorow i have my SATs the i don't know what i'm going to do. tonight i might go to bris i don't know if i am though. and tommrow night i'm supposed to stay at ashleys. then sunday me and kirsten and teagan are probably going to see corpse bride.

[mood| sleepy] [music|dance, dance - fall out boy ] last night's football game was so good. oh my gosh. anywho, i've been really busy with homework and basketball and stuff. last night i went to nicole's house and spent the night, it was pretty fun, except that i had to get up incredibly early in the morning for practice. i was supposed to go see the exorcism of emily rose with amanda, but that didn't really work out. there's a poker party tonight but i don't know if i'm going to go, because lauren is up and i should probably hang out with her. i don't know what's going on sunday except that i'm going to the movie in town with nicole. that's about all that's going on, but i got to do some homework, so peace out.

[mood| accomplished] so the first week of school wasn't bad, my classes are okay, but student assistant is my favorite. we had three games this week and we won all of them. last night at dowagic, haleigh fell adn dislocated her pinky it was disgusting, then ray ray fell and twisted her ankle through her ankle braces and all, but we still won. we don't have practice until monday which is cool. today i think i'm going to go to sporting image to get prices on the senior shirts so we can have people order them next week. but, that's about all i have to say.

[mood| artistic] You Know You're Too Big of a Harry Potter Fan When... ~You mutter nonsense latin words under your breath. ~You call your least favorite teacher Snape. ~Your computer says "You've Got Mail" and you run outside looking for an owl. ~You actually ask for a broom for Christmas. ~You mutter "lumos" under your breath every time you turn on a flashlight. ~You sort everyone you meet into the four Hogwarts houses. ~You were burned when you couldn't get through the flames of your fireplace. ~You had to go to the hospital after you broke your nose running headfirst into the wall between platforms nine and ten. ~The wand order mistake in GoF drove you crazy, and even after it was "corrected" you still came up with dozens of theories to explain why that happened. ~You point a normal things like parking meters and say "Look at the things these muggles dream up!" ~You collect plugs. ~You try on every piece of silvery fabric your mom has to see if you turn invisible ~Before getting up to get something, you always try to summon it first. Accio TV remote! ~You watched "Love, Actually" because two Harry Potter actors were in it. ~You were reduced to tears when you finally had book 5 in your hands. ~You refer to your Chemistry class as Potions. ~You spend hours tapping bricks in special orders hoping that a secret entrance to Diagon Alley will appear. ~When playing chess, you yell orders to the chess players and get upset when they don't move. ~You yell into the "fellytone." ~You get emotional every time you hear "Hedwig's Theme". ~You say "wicked" all the time because Rupert Grint does. ~You get thoroughly overexcited every time you see a word somewhere that is distantly linked with HP (ie. Saint Hedwig's). ~You name all of your pets after HP characters. ~You get in to heated arguments over how much gel Tom Felton had in his hair in the first two movies. ~You know that Harry's birthday is July 31, 1980, Hermione's birthday is September 19, 1979 and Ron's birthday is March 1, 1980 even though it never said in the books. ~You refer to Voldemort as "You-Know-Who", and no one has any idea who you're talking about. ~You went out and bought the latest editition of the Webster's Dictionary because they added the word "muggle". ~You were kicked out of the movie theater for standing on your chair, throwing your shoe at the screen and yelling "THAT DIDN'T HAPPEN IN THE BOOK!" ~You count the days until you're old enough for your apparating license, and everyone else thinks you're talking about driving. ~Your free time on the computer is spent constantly refreshing your favorite Harry Potter news site (MuggleNet, of course), hoping for an update.

i'm so excited. anywho, not much has been going on. but basketball conditioning starts tommorow, i'm not really worried, i've been running a mile every night and as long as that's all we have to run i'm good. i can handle the sprints and stuff. anyway, tommorow we're having a sugar bear employee sleepover at courtney's house. it should be fun, although i don't know if anyone is actually sleeping over. i might be getting a car soon, hopefully before basketball season. but other than that nothing exciting. well, i'm going to go. peace out.

so last night i went to laurens with ashley, mike and danny were there and we just played a bunch of games and hung out. it was fun. we played this game called spud it was fun, but tiring. then we played euchre and me and danny beat ashley and lauren 10-2 it was fun. after that we went to mcdonalds, but i wasn't hungry so i just got a shake. i have lots of pictures but i don't feel like posting them right now. so i'm going to go.

this weekend has been fun. on saturday i went shopping with carey and my mom. carey got a new scrapbook so she can start scrapbooking like crazy again. she also got a case for her camera then we went back to her house, but alison ditched us for kelly and david so we watched taking lives without her. anywho, today i went to the beach with emily, ashley, brian and brians brothers, it was fun but the lake was really cold. so we left earlier than planned and went swimming at ashley's house because the pool was warmer. ashley had to go to work at 5 so then i went home. at 6 bri called to see if i was going to basketball so we went, but there was none this weekend. so we went back to her house and asked alex and ali if they wanted to play they came over but the matt frownfelter and lil gump came over and they ruined our basketball because they wouldn't really play all they kept doing was immitating other people like geschke and fenner. it was dumb. 
so bri drops me off at home and went to alisons. after a while they came over and we watched the end of wimbeldon and then we went to alisons to watch the fireworks. we went on laurens boat for a while then we came in and lit off some fireworks and now i'm home and really tired and really burnt. but it was fun. well csi is on so i'm going to go. peace out.

so i haven't updated in like forever. not much has been going on. saturday/sunday was relay for life it was fun, i got to talk with patterson a lot, and carey came so that made me happy. kelly came and it seemed like forever since i saw her. then, on sunday i went to mattawan to play basketball it was fun, it always is. on monday i went little kids bball camp then swimming at alisons then to see bewitched with ali, bri and carey, it was an okay movie, i thought it would have been better, but after that we watched the seniors video because i'm in it. today i worked at the little kids camp then me goldberg and leduc went to taco bell then back to camp then i came home and fell asleep then i went to work. i don't know what is in store for the rest of the week so if anyone wants to hang out call me. peace out.

well, not much has been going on, i've just been going to grad parties and working on senior presents for the special few who get them. last night there was basketball at mattawan. it was fun we just scrimmaged. but i am so out of shape. i had a few good shots though. tonight and tommorow i have to work. but after that i don't have to work until sunday so i'm pretty happy about that. i went to see mr. and mrs. smith. it was good/funny. but right now i'm going to go watch a movie/do some exercise so i better go. peace out.

so this week has been crazy, school is finally out, one more year and hopefully i'll be getting out of this place. any who. wednesday after school me, haybag, bri, and ali made the nhs video, it was so corny/dumb. but after that i went over to ashley's house and laid out by the pool for a while. then thursday i went with lauren and ashley to kalamazoo/gallager's/hayloft. then on friday i went with emily and lauren to the beach. it was so relaxing. i loved it. after we left we dropped emily off then went to their apartment and did some crap then i went home. today i have to go to emily's party then to work then to my cousin's party. tommorow there is two grad parties and then basketball at mattawan, does anyone know what time that is. well i better get ready for homeE's party. peace out.
